<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Marc Abbyad</title><link>https://abbyad.com/</link><description>Recent content on Marc Abbyad</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><copyright>&lt;a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0&lt;/a></copyright><atom:link href="https://abbyad.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>About</title><link>https://abbyad.com/about/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://abbyad.com/about/</guid><description>&lt;p>I&amp;rsquo;ve long embraced the flexibility and excellence of &lt;strong>remote-first distributed teams&lt;/strong> (since 2010, not just 2020), but I prefer to live in the &lt;strong>mesaverse&lt;/strong>—a world grounded in real experiences. Whether I&amp;rsquo;m exploring nature and cities by foot, bike, or canoe, capturing photographs, throwing frisbees, or building treehouses, I embrace experiences that spark creativity and deepen my connection to the world around me. I thrive in &lt;strong>hands-on, in-person collaboration&lt;/strong>—whether solving problems, building things, or simply sharing ideas face-to-face.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Contact</title><link>https://abbyad.com/contact/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://abbyad.com/contact/</guid><description>&lt;p>Please reach out on &lt;a href="http://ca.linkedin.com/in/abbyad">LinkedIn&lt;/a> if you&amp;rsquo;d like to connect about work or collaborations, otherwise reach out on your platform of choice.&lt;/p>
